      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver version control and regression test suite documented; build verification log archived.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used under institutional license with version-controlled case files. Regression tests confirm consistent solver behaviour across patch releases. SQA documentation meets MRL 3 Gradation 2 expectations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Manufactured-solution or benchmark verification demonstrates solver solves governing equations correctly to second-order spatial accuracy.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy study on a lid-driven cavity benchmark confirms second-order convergence for velocity and pressure fields. Results consistent with published ANSYS verification suite."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI < 5% on hemolysis index QoI across three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh refinement study (coarse 4.2 M, medium 9.8 M, fine 21.3 M cells) yields GCI of 3.1% on the relative hemolysis index, satisfying the 5% threshold. Observed order of convergence p = 1.87."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature) documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump test data acquired at 5 L/min, 2500 RPM, 37 °C phosphate-buffered saline. Simulation boundary conditions replicate these within ±1% for flow rate and ±0.5% for rotational speed. Temperature dependence of viscosity accounted for."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) within 20% of experimental mean across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH deviates from experimental mean by 8–14% across the five operating points, comfortably within the 20% acceptance band. Agreement is consistent across flow-speed combinations, supporting model predictive capability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion and is computable from simulation outputs.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the primary regulatory metric for CPB device submissions. RH is derived directly from the CFD-predicted shear stress history integrated over particle pathlines, ensuring direct traceability to the decision criterion."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments use the same pump geometry, fluid analogue, and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under CPB-representative conditions. Fluid analogue (PBS with matched viscosity) and rotational speed range bracket the COU operating envelope. Geometric fidelity confirmed by independent CAD audit."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence and round-off error contributions to hemolysis QoI quantified and shown to be negligible relative to discretization error.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error assessment was considered beyond the scope of the current project phase. Residual convergence plots are available but formal quantification of iterative and round-off error contributions to the hemolysis QoI has not been performed. This gap is noted for future work."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented review process confirms simulation setup (boundary conditions, turbulence model selection, mesh topology) was independently verified by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "An independent analyst review of simulation setup was planned but not completed within the project timeline. Use error is considered low risk by the assessment team based on analyst experience, but no formal independent verification has been conducted. Deferred to the next assessment cycle."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparison of at least two models against experimental velocity profiles; power-law hemolysis model uncertainty bounded.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω and realizable k-ε models compared against PIV velocity data in the volute region. SST k-ω shows 7% lower RMS error and is selected. Hemolysis power-law exponent uncertainty propagated via ±10% parameter variation, yielding <6% change in NIH."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (blood viscosity, density) and geometric inputs documented with sources and uncertainty ranges.",
      "rationale": "Blood analogue viscosity measured at 37 °C (3.5 mPa·s ± 0.1 mPa·s) and density taken from literature (1060 kg/m³). Pump geometry digitised from FDA-released CAD files with dimensional verification against published drawings. Input uncertainty documented in the simulation plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sample-to-sample variability in experimental hemolysis measurements characterised and shown to be within acceptable bounds relative to simulation uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Only a single physical pump specimen was available for experimental testing. Sample-to-sample geometric variability and its effect on hemolysis measurement repeatability were not characterised. The assessment team considers this beyond scope given the use of the FDA reference geometry, but no supporting data have been gathered to substantiate this assumption."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters (boundary conditions, fluid properties) demonstrated to be equivalent to experimental conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profile derived from ultrasonic flow meter measurements upstream of the pump inlet. Outlet pressure boundary condition set to match measured back-pressure within ±2 mmHg. Fluid temperature controlled to 37 ± 0.5 °C in experiments and matched in simulation. Equivalency confirmed by parameter-by-parameter comparison table in the V&V report."
    }
  ],
